subSubSection.paragraph:
Anal appendages
. Dark brown. Cercus (superior appendages), in dorsal view (
Fig. 2d
), basally narrow, from basal 2/5 expanded inwards, then from its half gradually tapering distad; the apex round; the dorsal longitudinal ridge running from middle to the apex. Cercus, in lateral view (
Fig. 2e
), slender and gently warped downwards, with an obtusely shallow triangular ventral protrusion at apical forth. Epiproct (inferior appendage), about 0.72 times as the length of cercus, narrow triangle shape in dorsal view, and bow shape, warped downwards, in lateral view.
